						               													<description>Dungeon 6 could be considered as a masterless, dungeon delving, old-style RPG, in which one to six characters explore one of the many dangerous floors of the Hexagonal Tower, in order to retrieve the keys that can open the chamber of the Enigma Lord (the boss of the floor) and then defeat him.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every dungeon is progressively built using randomly extracted tiles representing corridors and (part of) rooms. Type and behavior of the encountered enemies are determined rolling a d6 and checking on the opportune tables.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dungeon 6 is also a campaign game: player characters can grow, improve their stats, and gain new and more powerful equipment. Every adventure has some specific text-based parts that will integrate with the basic rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dungeon 6 is a fantasy board game of dungeon exploring, epic battles and wonderful treasures, based on an easy system of procedural generation. Just throw a six-sided dice and see the game come alive: minimal setup time, maximum fun, infinite longevity!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the back of the box&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
